<h3>Component::<code>input-addon</code></h3>

<h4>Overview</h4>
<div class="row">
    <desc>
       The <code>input-addon</code> component is a helper component to the <code>input-wrapper</code> which builds prefix and postfix widgets. The key 
       inline properties are:
       <ul>
           <li><strong>style</strong>[string] - indicates a style family that will be used for the addon, default is 'bootstrap'</li>
           <li><strong>text</strong>[string] - puts text/label into the component</li>
           <li><strong>icon</strong>[string] - puts a font-based icon into the component</li>
           <li><strong>checkbox</strong>[boolean] - adds a checkbox to the component</li>
           <li><strong>radio</strong>[boolean] -  adds a radio choice to the component</li>
           <li><strong>button</strong>[boolean] adds a button to the component</li>
           <hr style="width:50%;text-align:left" />
           <li><strong>value</strong>[mixed] binds to the value of the checkbox/radio/choice selector</li>
       </ul>
       Other minor properties of note are:
       <ul>
           <li><strong>iconFirst</strong>[boolean] - determines whether an icon is diplayed first (aka, to left) or last (aka, to right)</li>
           <li>
               <strong>iconFamily</strong>[string] - typically the iconFamily would be static and set by user's ENV configuration 
               but if you want to be explicit about it who are we to stop you ... go nuts (expected values: 'fa' or 'glyphicons')
           </li>
       </ul>
       It is <em>not</em> expected that this component will be used externally to the <code>input-wrapper</code> and there are certain functions 
       like "sizing" which are actually controlled from the parent wrapper (by setting styles which impact this component) that are therefore not considered
       in scope for this addon directly. This design decision is largely inherited from the way that Twitter Bootstrap works and what works for the 
       goose (usually) works for the gander.
   </desc>
</div>

<h4>Example(s)</h4>

<examples>
            <widget>
            {{#input-wrapper size='large'}}
                {{input-addon 
                    style=style
                    text=text
                    icon=icon
                    checkbox=checkbox
                    radio=radio
                    button=button
                    value=value
                    iconFirst=iconFirst
                    iconFamily=iconFamily
                }}
                {{text-input placeholder='input-control'  style=style}} 
            {{/input-wrapper}}
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            {{#if checkbox}}Checkbox value: {{value}}{{/if}}
            </widget>
            <sourcecode>
                {{#code-block language="handlebars" poll=100}}
\{{#input-wrapper size='large'}}
    \{{input-addon 
        {{#if text}}text='{{text}}' 
        {{/if}}{{#if icon}}icon='{{icon}}' 
        {{/if}}{{#if checkbox}}checkbox={{checkbox}} 
        {{/if}}{{#if radio}}radio={{radio}} 
        {{/if}}{{#if button}}button={{button}}
        {{/if}}{{#if iconFirst}}iconFirst={{iconFirst}} 
        {{/if}}{{#if iconFirst}}iconFamily={{iconFamily}} 
        {{/if}}style='{{style}}'
    }}
    \{{text-input}}
\{{\input-wrapper}}   
                {{/code-block}}         
            </sourcecode>
</examples>

<configuration>
    <icon>{{icon-cog size="2x"}}</icon>
    <config>
        <columns>
            <column>
                Style:            
                {{ui-buttons choices='bootstrap,flat' selected=style}}<br/>
                iconFirst:            
                {{ui-toggle-button value=iconFirst}}<br/>
                iconFamily:            
                {{ui-buttons selected=iconFamily choices='fa,glyphicon'}}
            </column>
            <column>
                Text: {{text-input placeholder='text' width='150px' value=text}}<br/>
                Icon: {{text-input placeholder='icon' width='150px' value=icon}}<br/>
            </column>
            <column>
                {{ui-toggle-button value=checkbox}} Checkbox <br/>
                {{ui-toggle-button value=radio}} Radio <br/>
                {{ui-toggle-button value=button}} Button <br/>
            </column>                    
        </columns>
    </config>
</configuration>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<note>
    <strong>Note:</strong> 
    The implementations of <strong>radio</strong> and <strong>button</strong> ornamentations is not done yet
</note>